2.This code segment defines visualization parameters. min and max represent the minimum and maximum values of the data, while bands specify the bands to be displayed in the image. Here, three bands are used: ‘B4’, ‘B3’, and ‘B2’, corresponding to the red, green, and blue bands, typically employed for creating color images. The commented section provides another set of bands values, which comprise near-infrared, red, and green bands for false-color synthesis. This synthesis method is often utilized to emphasize features of specific objects such as vegetation, land, and water bodies. opacity indicates the transparency of the image.
