3.This code segment utilizes the GEE JavaScript API to process Sentinel-2 satellite imagery data and visualize it on a map. The code creates an ImageCollection of Sentinel-2 surface reflectance images. Then, it filters the collection to select images with cloud cover less than 15% within the specified time range and chooses the specified bands. Finally, it calculates the median of the images within the time range to produce a composite image. Additionally, the code computes the Normalized Difference Water Index (NDWI) and masks out pixels with NDWI values less than 0.3 from the composite image. It selects the specified bands from the processed image and adds it to the map for visualization.
dates.forEach(function(dateRange) {
  var start = dateRange.year + '-' + dateRange.month + '-01';
